<TITLE> Unis asked to run admissions online </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 11 (bdnews24.com)--The government on Friday asked all 31 public universities to conduct their admission activities online in 2009-10 academic year to reduce pressure of the admission seekers, an official handout said. The handout of the Press Information Department said (PID) said the move would help the students to collect and submit their admission application papers online. It also asked the universities to publish admission seating arrangement and results online, and said in case of collecting fee the institutions would have to get to mobile phone or online banking option
